	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Famitracker can be used to write music yes. It's how SivakD created his own soundtracks. It's for the slightly advanced user though, as figuring out how to create instruments can be tricky. Also you should know how to "track" (the process of creating tracked module files like S3M, IT, XM, etc)
<br />
<br />EDIT: Hmm Well it seems I figured out how to make a multiple NSF with all the S3M's into one big NSF.. think I should do one last release? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> heh

		

		</td>
	</tr>
